: variant of   Wilford  ."]}]},{"name":"Alice","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a variant of   Adelaide  , representing an Old French spelling of a reduced form of Germanic <i>Adalheidis</i>. <i>Alice</i> and <i>Adelaide</i> were already regarded as distinct names in English during the medieval period. <i>Alice</i> enjoyed a surge of popularity in the 19th century and periods of favour ever since. It was the name of the central character of  Lewis Carroll's  Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (  1865 ) and Through the Looking Glass (  1872 ), who was based on his child friend  Alice Liddell , daughter of the Dean of Christ Church, Oxford."],"variants":[{"name":"Alys","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alice ."]},{"name":"Alis","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Alice</b> ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Alice Wilford was born in 1500, in Amersham, Buckinghamshire, England, United Kingdom. She had at least 1 son with Sir Richard Saunders. She died in 1543, in her hometown, at the age of 43, and was buried in Amersham, Buckinghamshire, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1500–1543":"1500–1543","1487–1524":"1487–1524","1500–Male":"1500–Surnud","1504–Female":"1504–Surnud","1510–1555":"1510–1555","1522–Male":"1522–Surnud","1524":"1524","1500":"1500","1522":"1522","1555":"1555","1510":"1510","1543":"1543","1487":"1487","01 OCT 1524":"11. oktoober 1524","about 1522":"umbes 1522","1504":"1504","Agmondesham,, Buckinghamshire, England":"Amersham with Coleshill, Buckinghamshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Amersham, Buckinghamshire, England":"Amersham, Buckinghamshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"England","Staffordshire, England":"Staffordshire, England","Amersham, Chiltern District, Buckinghamshire, England":"Amersham, Buckinghamshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1500–1543":"1500–1543","1487–1524":"1487–1524","1500–Male":"1500–Kuollut","1504–Female":"1504–Kuollut","1510–1555":"15